This paper deals with the capacity analysis of wireless ad-hoc networks with MIMO techniques, which is a topic related to network information theory (cs.IT) and network optimization (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of MMSE receivers, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.MM). The analysis of interference and spatial resource allocation is relevant to system engineering (cs.SY) and performance evaluation (cs.PF).
